verses.text:
Take ye the sum of all the congregation of the children of
Israel, after their families, by the house of their fathers, with the
number of \add their\add* names, every male by their polls;

So were all those that were numbered of the children of Israel,
by the house of their fathers, from twenty years old and upward,
all that were able to go forth to war in Israel;

And I, behold, I have taken the Levites from among the children
of Israel instead of all the firstborn that openeth the matrix among the
children of Israel: therefore the Levites shall be mine;

Take the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the children
of Israel, and the cattle of the Levites instead of their cattle;
and the Levites shall be mine: I \add am\add* the \nd LORD\nd*.

And for those that are to be redeemed of the two hundred and threescore and
thirteen of the firstborn of the children of Israel, which are more
than the Levites;

Of the firstborn of the children of Israel took he the money;
a thousand three hundred and threescore and five \add shekels\add*,
after the shekel of the sanctuary:

Speak unto the children of Israel, When a man or woman shall
commit any sin that men commit, to do a trespass against the \nd LORD\nd*,
and that person be guilty;

And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel;
and of the dust that is in the floor of the tabernacle the priest
shall take, and put \add it\add* into the water:

And the Levites were purified, and they washed their clothes;
and Aaron offered them \add as\add* an offering before the \nd LORD\nd*;
and Aaron made an atonement for them to cleanse them.

And the sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow with the trumpets;
and they shall be to you for an ordinance for ever throughout your
generations.

And it came to pass, when the ark set forward, that Moses
said, Rise up, \nd LORD\nd*, and let thine enemies be scattered;
and let them that hate thee flee before thee.

And see the land, what it \add is;\add* and the people that
dwelleth therein, whether they \add be\add* strong or weak, few or
many;

And what the land \add is\add* that they dwell in, whether it
\add be\add* good or bad; and what cities \add they be\add* that they
dwell in, whether in tents, or in strong holds;

Because all those men which have seen my glory, and my miracles,
which I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and have tempted me now these
ten times, and have not hearkened to my voice;

But my servant Caleb, because he had another spirit with him, and hath
followed me fully, him will I bring into the land whereinto he went;
and his seed shall possess it.

Speak unto Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest, that he take
up the censers out of the burning, and scatter thou the fire yonder;
for they are hallowed.

And when Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the
priest, saw \add it\add*, he rose up from among the congregation,
and took a javelin in his hand;

Take the sum of all the congregation of the children of Israel,
from twenty years old and upward, throughout their fathers’ house,
all that are able to go to war in Israel.

¶ Reuben, the eldest son of Israel: the children of Reuben;
Hanoch, \add of whom cometh\add* the family of the Hanochites: of
Pallu, the family of the Palluites:

The daughters of Zelophehad speak right: thou shalt surely
give them a possession of an inheritance among their father’s brethren;
and thou shalt cause the inheritance of their father to pass unto them.

¶ And the \nd LORD\nd* said unto Moses, Take thee Joshua the
son of Nun, a man in whom \add is\add* the spirit, and lay thine
hand upon him;

¶ And in the beginnings of your months ye shall offer a burnt
offering unto the \nd LORD\nd*; two young bullocks, and one ram,
seven lambs of the first year without spot;

And three tenth deals of flour \add for\add* a meat offering,
mingled with oil, for one bullock; and two tenth deals of flour \add for\add*
a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one ram;

And their meat offering \add shall be of\add* flour mingled
 with oil: three tenth deals shall ye offer for a bullock, and two
tenth deals for a ram;

But ye shall offer the burnt offering for a sweet savour unto the
\nd LORD\nd*; two young bullocks, one ram, seven lambs of the first
year;

¶ And Eleazar the priest said unto the men of war which went
to the battle, This \add is\add* the ordinance of the law which the
\nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses;

And the asses \add were\add* thirty thousand and five hundred;
of which the \nd LORD’s\nd* tribute \add was\add* threescore and
one.

And they shall be unto you cities for refuge from the avenger;
that the manslayer die not, until he stand before the congregation
in judgment.
